abstract: Only now am I starting to see Mom as someone other than my mother, and the older I get the more right she is.
snippet: Only now am I starting to see Mom as someone other than my mother, and the older I get the more right she is.
lead_paragraph: It was my husband’s first trip to my hometown of Snellville, Ga., and to ensure that we’d return, my mother was determined to show us a good time.

abstract: Technology developed for warfare finds surprising civilian applications, including surveys of wildlife populations.
snippet: Technology developed for warfare finds surprising civilian applications, including surveys of wildlife populations.
lead_paragraph: Monte Vista National Wildlife Refuge, Colo. — An electric whir filled the air of this high desert valley as Jeff Sloan, a cartographer for the United States Geological Survey, hurled a small remote-controlled airplane into the sky. The plane, a four-and-a-half-pound AeroVironment Raven, dipped; then its plastic propeller whined and pulled it into the sky.

abstract: Hunger strike by Guantánamo prisoners; a premier is nominated in Italy; dying trees in Japan; ballet spreads in the Middle East.
snippet: Hunger strike by Guantánamo prisoners; a premier is nominated in Italy; dying trees in Japan; ballet spreads in the Middle East.
lead_paragraph: NEWS With any decision about closing down the prison in Guantánamo Bay, Cuba, put on the back burner, inmates there have lost hope that they will ever be released. A hunger strike is now in its third month, with 93 prisoners considered to be participating — more than half the inmates. Charlie Savage reports from Guantánamo Bay, Cuba.

abstract: John Idzik, the new general manager, has a defined sense of what he wants in a player he is about to draft, and he has plenty of openings.
snippet: John Idzik, the new general manager, has a defined sense of what he wants in a player he is about to draft, and he has plenty of openings.
lead_paragraph: John Idzik worked in the Tampa Bay front office in 1997 when the Buccaneers set out in the draft to improve the N.F.L.’s lowest-scoring offense. They focused on a certain running back, and after ascertaining that another team was also in pursuit, they maneuvered to select him with the 12th pick.

abstract: Karl Mueller talks about his horror film “Mr. Jones,” part of the Midnight Section at this year’s Tribeca Film Festival.
snippet: Karl Mueller talks about his horror film “Mr. Jones,” part of the Midnight Section at this year’s Tribeca Film Festival.
lead_paragraph: Growing up in a small Minnesota town, the director Karl Mueller had plenty of inspiration for his indie horror movie “Mr. Jones,” part of this year’s Midnight Section of the Tribeca Film Festival. The film is set at a remote house where a couple, played by Jon Foster and Sarah Jones, goes up against unseen forces unleashed when they encounter an eccentric artist neighbor known as Mr. Jones (Mark Steger).
